    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-15T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-15T05:00:00-05:00" n="677"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d677">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.20/11–1549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hong Kong</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rankin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hong Kong</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-15T18:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 15, 1949—6 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 15—11:26 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1050. We are informed by American journalists recently Hainan that there are
                    about 100,000 Nationalist troops in Hoihow area who are refugees from adjacent
                    mainland. Troops are virtually out of control, units mixed and discipline bad,
                    with crimes of violence common.</p>
                <p>Chen Chi-tang<note n="67" xml:id="d677fn67">Governor of Hainan Island.</note>
                    informed journalists he lacks rice feed these troops and funds pay them. Has
                    been supporting local government from private funds which are almost exhausted.
                    Has unsuccessfully applied to Generalissimo for help meet this situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rankin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
